      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel) computed with uncertainty intervals for hemolysis index at all operating points; systematic bias assessed.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison was performed at two operating points only; bias analysis is incomplete and prediction intervals were not propagated. Achieved level 2 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Hemolysis index predicted by the model is directly the clinical QoI; no surrogate or indirect mapping is used.",
      "rationale": "The model predicts normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) which maps to clinical QoI, but the mapping from computational scalar transport to NIH introduces an empirical power-law correlation with unquantified uncertainty. Achieved level 3 is below required level 5."
    },
